<div class="question-card" id="card-59" data-qid="59" data-type="multi">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 60</span>
    <span class="q-tag multi">Choose 2</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      A network technician is researching the use of fiber optic cabling in a new technology center. Which two issues should be considered before implementing fiber optic media? (Choose two.)
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-59">
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Fiber optic cabling requires different termination and splicing expertise from what copper cabling requires.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Fiber optic cabling requires specific grounding to be immune to EMI.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Fiber optic cabling is susceptible to loss of signal due to RFI.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Fiber optic provides higher data capacity but is more expensive than copper cabling.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="4">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">E</span>
        <span class="opt-text">Fiber optic cable is able to withstand rough handling.</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn" id="submit-59" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-59">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-59"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        Fiber optic media is more expensive than copper cabling used over the same distance. Fiber optic cables use light instead of an electrical signal, so EMI and RFI are not issues. However, fiber optic does require different skills to terminate and splice.
      </div>
    </div>
